social_posts.post_text: We’ve been busy elves decking the halls, checking our lists, and trimming the tree over at @staggdesign . Today we’re sharing a little holiday home tour from our resident stylist Melissa.🎄

Merry Christmas from our family to you!  It has been one of our more challenging years, but we are heading into 2023 with the girls’ energy in the second photo 🤗😎😁

Wishing you love, peace, health, and happiness in the year ahead! 

📸 @veronicamiehlke

Closing out the dumpster fire of 2022 with an actual fire at #staggmountainmodern 🔥🔥🔥. First let me say, no one was hurt and thanks to our amazing neighbors quick actions, firefighters who were there in minutes, and what I believe was divine intervention with the strong storm winds blowing in exactly the right direction, our home was mostly saved.  The firefighters kept telling us what a miracle it was the fire didn’t take the house 😭😭😭

One of our contractors accidentally left some equipment on in their trailer, which overheated just before 4 am, and literally exploded.  The sound awoke our neighbors who leapt into action, calling 911 and awaking us.  It took less than 10 minutes for the fire to start moving to the house, and without them acting so quickly, our home would have been destroyed.

This is not how we envisioned ringing in the new year, but tonight as we watch the clock strike midnight, we are filled with gratitude.  For the miracles we witnessed early this morning, for our health after a very challenging year full of curveballs, and for each other.  Hey 2023, let’s just chill the freak out, eh?

Boy, are we counting our blessings today.  When you see just how close the trailer was to our house, you know how hard the wind was blowing, and how quickly the fire exploded, it’s pretty unbelievable that the damage is contained to just one section of #staggmountainmodern .

Is this a setback? Yes, but we hope not a major one.

Did I have a sleepless night with ptsd, worrying about what horrible thing could happen next?  Yes, but the snow blanketing our home today felt like a fresh, clean start to the year, and I’m clinging to that today.

2022 was filled with a lot of unexpectedly stressful and traumatic life events, and this fire feels like a twisted grand finale to a year we are so ready to be over.  There have been many days we’ve felt broken and defeated.  But as we look hopefully at the new year ahead, I’m filled mostly with gratitude. 

We will never again take for granted the feeling of peace, the absence of fear, the blessings of good health, the closeness of our little family, and a warm, beautiful, comforting place to call home.  We are walking into 2023 covered in soot, but we are rising from the ashes.  However that Honey Bucket isn’t bouncing back from this…..

Renovate a house, we said.  It will be so FUN.  This is just us, having SO. MUCH. FUN.

I’ve shared little bits of just how hard our latest renovation has been, but the truth is it’s truly been the toughest year and a half of our lives.  I get questions daily about our house, asking me to share more.  Why haven’t I?  Well, it’s complicated.  I’ve written and rewritten a blog post about it about a dozen times, and I think I’m finally ready to push publish.  The link is in my bio if you want to read more.

Thank you to those of you who have cheered us on, shared our work, and who have told me you’re invested in our project.  I wish we were nearing the finish line, but the fire has thrown a major wrench in the progress (more on that later). Cheers to doing (very) hard things!  We are battered and bruised but still forging ahead!

Don’t have a love interest? Want to spend Valentine’s with your girlfriends? We’ve got just the solution: a Galentine’s Party! 

Today, on the blog, our resident Stagg Design Stylist and party expert, Melissa is sharing one of her favorite traditions- a Valentine’s party all about the girls. ♥️
Exciting progress is happening at our @staggdesign client’s new build #projectworththewait We’re giving you a behind the scenes look of the process and it’s lookin’ 😎

LISTEN, renovating a neglected home during a pandemic and supply chain nightmare with snow storms, downpours, rodents, mold, and a fire ain’t for sissies.  But the best things are worth fighting for.  We are in countdown mode to move in (our lease on our rental is up soon and we aren’t renewing!). An update on #staggmountainmodern is live on www.staggdesign.com and I’m sharing our timeline!  Send the good vibes this way because one way or another, we’re moving in! 

#renovation #interiordesign #staggdesign

Future home of a puppy wash 🐶🫧 Sharing the plans for our dog wash station today on www.staggdesign.com and our rendering for this space!  You guys are coming in 🔥with the dog tips in stories!  Can you see the vision for this spot?

READ TO THE END 😳
We have the squirrel in custody!!! Last night we watched this little jerk climb right up the same spot and into the soffit.  Jon pulled out the trap and he went for the apples, almonds, and flower added by Vivie because she was sure he would smell it.  He is frantic in the cage, so we are going to set him loose in the woods.  The plan is to drive far up the canyon and set him free because we aren’t squirrel murderers.  Now if it was a mouse or rat, that would be a different story.  Not today, squirrel!!! 

***update:  shortly after this, we noticed the squirrel had stopped moving, and Jon was sure he had just tired himself out from running back and forth in the cage.  Nope.  He was dead.  You guys.  He had freaked out TO DEATH.  And if that’s not a metaphor for what we are absolutely NOT going to be doing over all the issues we’ve had with the construction process, I don’t know what is.  RIP, squirrel.  We feel sad you died, but we do not feel sad that you’re not in our house.

We’re finally in the home stretch of our @staggdesign client’s new build that has been years in the making. Our team is counting down the days until we get to install this beauty! #projectworththewait

Whether you're wanting to renovate the home you grew up in, build from the ground up, or spruce up your current house, we've got you covered. We work with our clients to transform their homes into a place they never want to leave. The "heart" of each home guides our design process and that sets our work apart. Stagg Design combines good design with soul and feeling, and you can feel the difference in the finished product. We believe home is what we make it-- so let's make yours truly you.

We’re currently booking new clients and we’d love to hear about your project! Get in touch at staggdesign.com to start the design process.

The mirrors went up in the #staggmountainmodern dance studio/workout room today and it took my breath away.  The windows look out across the valley all the way to the Great Salt Lake and the natural light feels so healing.  There are a lot of areas in the home we could have put our resources toward first, but this one felt like a big priority with summer now here.  Already planning the first dance party!  And just wait until you see the lighting in here 😍
We are nearing the finish line on our @staggdesign #projectworththewait and boy, she lookin’ fiiiiiine!

Looking for an easy and affordable way to decorate your outdoor space for the 4th of July? Our @staggdesign stylist Melissa has rounded up her favorite pieces so you can add a touch of red, white, and blue to your patio. Shop all of our 4th of July picks in stories! 🇺🇸
We’re bringing you along on a site visit to check in on progress at our @staggdesign client’s project. Get a behind the scenes look at #projectworththewait in our stories!

BEFORE ➡️ NOW ✨

Ya’ll have been asking for a #staggmountainmodern update, and here’s a big one!  We have been busy over here completely transforming the yard before the weather changes.  Watch for a breakdown on stories— it was quite the project, and we aren’t finished yet!
A versatile, simple porch styling you can use throughput Fall with just a few simple switches in and out! Head over to our stories to shop the look.

This Fall charcuterie board is the perfect crowd pleaser to bring to your next gathering. Just arrange your favorite seasonal cheeses, fresh fruit, nuts, olives, crackers, and jams together. Tap the post for serving ware we used to create the look. 🍁🍂

The moody, rainy weather here has us feeling spooky.  I’m breaking all kinds of rules showing you the lower level family room before the official reveal (and process), but whatevs.  I like to live life on the edge 💀

Have a question about this room?  Drop it below!  Hatching plans for showing how we renovated this space starting tomorrow!  And check out stories for more! #staggmountainmodern

When you’re working with an old house, it takes some imagination to dream up something new from something old.  May I present the lower level fireplace makeover. 

Any guesses what the material is?  Hint: you’ll be surprised!! Comment below! 

#staggmountainmodern

Today we’re sharing the step-by-step process of our lower level fireplace design. 

Step 1: demo
Step 2: rebuild the frame
Step 3: tile
Step 4: clean and paint the interior with high heat spray paint
Step 5: marble installation
Step 6: clean up!

The next step will be putting fire cannon balls in place and hooking up the gas line again.

Head on over to our stories for all the details!
#staggmountainmodern

I’ve been anxiously awaiting our home’s exterior to be far enough along to decorate for Halloween and we made it just before pumpkins sold out everywhere 🫠 It may not be perfect, BUT a festive porch makes me so happy!  AND you’re getting a peek at the exterior work!  Double win!
Behind the scenes from our latest site visit to a nearly completed #projectworththewait

Just over here sharing things all out of order, but seeing those floors come to life is so rewarding!  I’ve been dreaming of this color combination for years.  Any guesses which room this is?? #staggmountainmodern

I don’t love jumping to full Christmas mode right after Halloween, and like to create a transition from fall and Thanksgiving to Christmas.  By making a few simple switches after Halloween, my porches feel ready for the next holiday!  What do you think?  Are you team transition or full Christmas? (No wrong answers!)! Shop these looks in stories! #staggmountainmodern

How about a little “BEFORE” and “NOW”? 😱

We can’t believe it’s the same house sometimes!  There’s still a ways to go on the exterior, and we are racing to finish it before the weather changes.  Here’s the very long list of what has changed on the exterior:

* cut down over a hundred trees
* addition above the garage
* took down the old pergola
* new windows
* new retaining walls, steel planter, stairs, pavers 
* new front door
* put in a slider where windows used to be
* new walkway
* patched and painted brick 
* stucco plaster repair and addition
* new lighting 
* painted garage doors
* new landscaping, sprinkler system, etc 
* siding going up as we speak!

Phew!  Probably missing a few things!  What a transformation, amiright?

It’s wild to remember just how far each part of our house has come.  The original doors felt so heavy and dark.  But these custom steel and glass doors are magic!  They let in so much light and feel airy and fresh! #staggmountainmodern

Exactly one year ago, New Years Eve, a contractor’s trailer exploded in the middle of the night and our house caught on fire.  It was a very windy night and our house went up in minutes.  The explosion woke up our sweet neighbors who called 911 and whose quick thinking saved the house.  It was traumatic and a real pain in the 🍑 clean up, as we battled the insurance company.  Something I didn’t share was that the contractor cashed out with the insurance company, and disappeared, leaving us to clean up his mess from the fire and his work.  It was disheartening to say the least.

Tonight, we are snuggled up together in our home, watching Harry Potter and doing puzzles, and praying for a much less explosive start to 2024.  Hey universe, please take it easy on us.  We could use a really chill year. 😎
A moment for the stairs from our @staggdesign client #projectworththewait
